                <tr>
                  <td rowspan="5">III</td>
                  <td rowspan="5">Fundamental Rights</td>
                  <td>13</td>
                  <td><a href="#">Laws inconsistent with or in derogation of the fundamental rights</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>15</td>
                  <td><a href="#">Prohibition of discrimination on grounds of religion, race, caste, sex or place of birth</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>21A</td>
                  <td><a href="#">Right to education</a> <br><small>[Inserted by the 86th Amendment in December, 2002 and passed by the Parliament in July, 2009. The provisions of the Act came into force from 1st April, 2010]</small></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>28</td>
                  <td><a href="#">Freedom as to attendance at religious instruction or religious worship in certain educational institutions</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>30</td>
                  <td><a href="#">Right of minorities to establish and administer educational institutions</a></td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>

